6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. K.S.A. 8-15,106 is hereby amended to read as follows: 8-
8 15,106. (a) It shall be unlawful for any person to operate a micro utility
9 truck: (1) on any interstate highway, or federal highway or state highway;
10 or (2) on any public highway or street within the corporate limits of any
11 city unless authorized by such city.
12 (b) No micro utility truck shall be operated on any public highway or
13 street, unless such truck complies with the equipment requirements under
14 article 17 of chapter 8 of the Kansas Statutes Annotated, and amendments
15 theretoA person may operate a micro utility truck on any state or public
16 highway or street under the following conditions:
17 (1) The micro utility truck shall be properly registered under article 1
18 of chapter 8 of the Kansas Statutes Annotated, and amendments thereto;
19 (2) the micro utility truck shall comply with the equipment
20 requirements under article 17 of chapter 8 of the Kansas Statutes
21 Annotated, and amendments thereto; and
22 (3) the micro utility truck shall only be operated on a state or public
23 highway with a posted maximum speed limit of 65 miles per hour or less.
24 (c) The provisions of subsection (a), shall not prohibit a micro utility
25 truck from crossing a federal or state highway.
26 (d) This section shall be a part of and supplemental to the uniform act
27 regulating traffic on highways.
28 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 8-15,106 is hereby repealed.
29 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
30 publication in the statute book.

